Common Mistakes That Make SaaS Emails Feel Automated
Even well-intentioned teams often make mistakes that make messaging feel robotic. Some of the most common pitfalls include:

Overusing templates
Templates are helpful, but overreliance leads to sameness. Readers can sense template-based emails instantly.

Using unnatural or overly complex language
Corporate buzzwords create distance between you and the reader.

Ignoring mobile optimization
Most U.S. business leaders read emails on their phones. Long blocks of text hurt readability.

Overselling
Aggressive language damages credibility.

Lack of clarity
Buyers want to understand your value quickly. Unclear messages lead to immediate deletion.

No personalization
Generic messages feel irrelevant.

Poor follow-up timing
Too many automated follow-ups create fatigue.

Humanizing your copy eliminates these issues.

